# ============================================================
# pre-push — last-line-of-defense before the commit reaches the
# remote.
#
# Runs the typecheck + test suites on the entire workspace.
# Slower than pre-commit (10-30s typical) but catches the kind
# of regression that lint-staged can't see — a hook-order bug
# in StationList, a missing translation key, a broken test in
# a file the commit didn't touch but transitively breaks.
#
# This is intentionally NOT in pre-commit because per-commit
# typechecking creates friction that pushes devs toward
# --no-verify. Pre-push is the right boundary: rebases / WIP
# commits stay fast, but `git push` is checked.
#
# Skip with `git push --no-verify` only when you know what
# you're doing (e.g. pushing a WIP branch you're about to
# rebase before opening a PR).
# ============================================================
npm run -w @fuelyn/core type-check
npm run -w @fuelyn/web type-check
npm run -w @fuelyn/core test
npm run -w @fuelyn/web test
